TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi beforefieldinit BlobProperties extends System.Object

Docs.summary: Properties of a Blob.

MemberSignature.Value: .method public hidebysig specialname rtspecialname instance void .ctor() cil managed

Docs.summary: Constructor.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AcceptRanges As String

Docs.summary: Indicates that the service supports requests for partial blob content.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AccessTier As String

Docs.summary:
The tier of page blob on a premium storage account or tier of block blob on blob storage LRS accounts. For a list of allowed premium page blob tiers, see . For general purpose v2 and blob storage account types, the valid values are:
Hot
Cool
Archive

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AccessTierChangedOn As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: The time the tier was changed on the object. This is only returned if the tier on the block blob was ever set.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AccessTierInferred As Boolean

Docs.summary: For page blobs on a premium storage account only. If the access tier is not explicitly set on the blob, the tier is inferred based on its content length and this header will be returned with true value.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ArchiveStatus As String

Docs.summary: For blob storage LRS accounts, valid values are rehydrate-pending-to-hot/rehydrate-pending-to-cool. If the blob is being rehydrated and is not complete then this header is returned indicating that rehydrate is pending and also tells the destination tier.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property BlobCommittedBlockCount As Integer

Docs.summary: The number of committed blocks present in the blob. This header is returned only for append blobs.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property BlobCopyStatus As Nullable(Of CopyStatus)

Docs.summary: State of the most recent copy operation identified by x-ms-copy-id, if any.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property BlobSequenceNumber As Long

Docs.summary: The current sequence number for a page blob. This header is not returned for block blobs or append blobs.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property BlobType As BlobType

Docs.summary: The blob's type.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CacheControl As String

Docs.summary: This header is returned if it was previously specified for the blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ContentDisposition As String

Docs.summary: This header returns the value that was specified for the 'x-ms-blob-content-disposition' header. The Content-Disposition response header field conveys additional information about how to process the response payload, and also can be used to attach additional metadata. For example, if set to attachment, it indicates that the user-agent should not display the response, but instead show a Save As dialog with a filename other than the blob name specified.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ContentEncoding As String

Docs.summary: This header returns the value that was specified for the Content-Encoding request header.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ContentHash As Byte()

Docs.summary: If the blob has an MD5 hash and this operation is to read the full blob, this response header is returned so that the client can check for message content integrity.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ContentLanguage As String

Docs.summary: This header returns the value that was specified for the Content-Language request header.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ContentLength As Long

Docs.summary: The number of bytes present in the response body.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ContentType As String

Docs.summary: The content type specified for the blob. The default content type is 'application/octet-stream'.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CopyCompletedOn As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Conclusion time of the last attempted Copy Blob operation where this blob was the destination blob. This value can specify the time of a completed, aborted, or failed copy attempt. This header does not appear if a copy is pending, if this blob has never been the destination in a Copy Blob operation, or if this blob has been modified after a concluded Copy Blob operation using Set Blob Properties, Put Blob, or Put Block List.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CopyId As String

Docs.summary: String identifier for this copy operation. Use with Get Blob Properties to check the status of this copy operation, or pass to Abort Copy Blob to abort a pending copy.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CopyProgress As String

Docs.summary: Contains the number of bytes copied and the total bytes in the source in the last attempted Copy Blob operation where this blob was the destination blob. Can show between 0 and Content-Length bytes copied. This header does not appear if this blob has never been the destination in a Copy Blob operation, or if this blob has been modified after a concluded Copy Blob operation using Set Blob Properties, Put Blob, or Put Block List.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CopySource As Uri

Docs.summary: URL up to 2 KB in length that specifies the source blob or file used in the last attempted Copy Blob operation where this blob was the destination blob. This header does not appear if this blob has never been the destination in a Copy Blob operation, or if this blob has been modified after a concluded Copy Blob operation using Set Blob Properties, Put Blob, or Put Block List.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CopyStatus As CopyStatus

Docs.summary: Legacy facade for . State of the copy operation identified by x-ms-copy-id.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CopyStatusDescription As String

Docs.summary: Only appears when x-ms-copy-status is failed or pending. Describes the cause of the last fatal or non-fatal copy operation failure. This header does not appear if this blob has never been the destination in a Copy Blob operation, or if this blob has been modified after a concluded Copy Blob operation using Set Blob Properties, Put Blob, or Put Block List

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CreatedOn As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Returns the date and time the blob was created.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property DestinationSnapshot As String

Docs.summary: Included if the blob is incremental copy blob or incremental copy snapshot, if x-ms-copy-status is success. Snapshot time of the last successful incremental copy snapshot for this blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property EncryptionKeySha256 As String

Docs.summary: The SHA-256 hash of the encryption key used to encrypt the metadata. This header is only returned when the metadata was encrypted with a customer-provided key.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property EncryptionScope As String

Docs.summary: Returns the name of the encryption scope used to encrypt the blob contents and application metadata. Note that the absence of this header implies use of the default account encryption scope.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ETag As ETag

Docs.summary: The ETag contains a value that you can use to perform operations conditionally. If the request version is 2011-08-18 or newer, the ETag value will be in quotes.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ExpiresOn As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: The time this blob will expire.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property HasLegalHold As Boolean

Docs.summary: Indicates if the blob has a legal hold.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ImmutabilityPolicy As BlobImmutabilityPolicy

Docs.summary: The associated with the blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property IsIncrementalCopy As Boolean

Docs.summary: Included if the blob is incremental copy blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property IsLatestVersion As Boolean

Docs.summary: The value of this header indicates whether version of this blob is a current version, see also x-ms-version-id header.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property IsSealed As Boolean

Docs.summary: If this blob has been sealed.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property IsServerEncrypted As Boolean

Docs.summary: The value of this header is set to true if the blob data and application metadata are completely encrypted using the specified algorithm. Otherwise, the value is set to false (when the blob is unencrypted, or if only parts of the blob/application metadata are encrypted).

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property LastAccessed As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Returns the date and time the blob was read or written to.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property LastModified As DateTimeOffset

Docs.summary: Returns the date and time the blob was last modified. Any operation that modifies the blob, including an update of the blob's metadata or properties, changes the last-modified time of the blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property LeaseDuration As LeaseDurationType

Docs.summary: When a blob is leased, specifies whether the lease is of infinite or fixed duration.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property LeaseState As LeaseState

Docs.summary: Lease state of the blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property LeaseStatus As LeaseStatus

Docs.summary: The current lease status of the blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Metadata As IDictionary(Of String, String)

Docs.summary: Metadata.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ObjectReplicationDestinationPolicyId As String

Docs.summary: Object Replication Policy Id of the destination blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ObjectReplicationSourceProperties As IList(Of ObjectReplicationPolicy)

Docs.summary: Parsed Object Replication Policy Id, Rule Id(s) and status of the source blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property RehydratePriority As String

Docs.summary: If this blob is in rehydrate pending state, this indicates the rehydrate priority.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property TagCount As Long

Docs.summary: The number of tags associated with the blob.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property VersionId As String

Docs.summary: A DateTime value returned by the service that uniquely identifies the blob. The value of this header indicates the blob version, and may be used in subsequent requests to access this version of the blob.
